{% extends "_layouts/blog.jinja" %}

{% block page_content %}

<h3 id="intro">Intro</h3>
<p>
  {{ link::e(path="https://fontawesome.com/", description="Font Awesome") }}

  is a collection of great looking icons that 
  we can use to spice up the look of our app.
</p>

{{ text::note_block(text='
   There is a free version and a paid version. In this post we will be 
  utilizing the free version of Font Awesome.
')
}}

<h3 id="software">Software</h3>
<p>
  The following software versions were used in this post.
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Rails - 6.0.3.4</li>
  <li>Font Awesome (Free) - 5.15.1</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="installation">Installation</h3>
{{ text::note_block(text='
  In a previous $1
  I added the Bootstrap (5) CSS framework to a Rails 6 app.
  For context on the file placement of the Font Awesome 
  package, you might want to check that post out first.
')
  | replace(from="$1", to=link::i(path="/blog/add-bootstrap-5-to-a-rails-6-app", description="post"))
}}

<p>
  Firstly add the {{ text::emphasize(text="fontawesome-free") }}

  package via yarn.
</p>
{{ text::code_block(
  header="cmd",
  language="text",
  code='yarn add @fortawesome/fontawesome-free'
) }}

<p>
  Next, we import the Font Awesome package into our 
  {{ text::emphasize(text="application.css") }}

  file.
</p>
{{ text::code_block(
  header="file",
  language="css",
  code='/* app/assets/stylesheets/application.css */

@import "@fortawesome/fontawesome-free";'
) }}

<p>
  Finally, we import the Font Awesome package into 
  our {{ text::emphasize(text="application.js") }}
 
  file.
</p>

{{ text::code_block(
  header="file",
  language="javascript",
  code='// app/javascript/packs/application.js

import "@fortawesome/fontawesome-free/js/all";'
) }}

<h3 id="usage">Usage</h3>
<p>
  To find icons search for them 
  {{ link::e(path="https://fontawesome.com/icons?d=gallery", description="here") }}.
  Once you have an icon, add the HTML markup to 
  a page.
</p>
{{ text::code_block(
  header="file",
  language="html",
  code='&lt;i class="fab fa-instagram"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;'
) }}

<p>
  You can also change the size by adding extra size 
  classes to the tag. 
  {{ text::emphasize(text="fa-2x") }}
 in the 
  below example.
</p>
{{ text::code_block(
  header="file",
  language="html",
  code='&lt;i class="fab fa-instagram fa-2x"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;'
) }}


<h3 id="outro">Outro</h3>
<p>
  That's it. Not alot to it. now, make like Bill and 
  Ted and be excellent to each other.
</p>
{% endblock page_content %}